# Phase 4.2: Mobile Layout & Responsiveness Polish

## Viewport Configuration

- [x] Verify viewport meta tag in main layout file
  ```html
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  ```

## Responsive Testing with Chrome DevTools

- [ ] Enable Device Toolbar testing
  - Open Chrome DevTools (F12)
  - Enable "Device Toolbar" (Ctrl+Shift+M or Cmd+Shift+M)

### Test Common Mobile Screen Sizes
- [ ] Video Feed Layout
  - Verify videos are sized correctly
  - Check vertical swipe smoothness
  - Ensure proper spacing and alignment

- [ ] SwipeCard Responsiveness
  - Verify layout adapts to mobile screens
  - Check metadata readability
  - Test swipe gesture intuitiveness

- [ ] Navigation Bar
  - Verify bottom NavBar fits mobile screens
  - Check touch targets are appropriate size
  - Ensure no overlap with content

- [ ] Text Readability
  - Verify text is legible on smaller screens
  - Check font sizes using TailwindCSS responsive modifiers
  - Ensure proper contrast ratios

## Mobile-First TailwindCSS Implementation

- [ ] Review base mobile styles
  - Verify default styles (no prefixes) are mobile-optimized
  - Check padding and margins are appropriate for mobile

- [ ] Responsive Design Implementation
  - Use sm:, md:, lg:, xl: prefixes for larger screen adjustments
  - Verify progressive enhancement approach
  - Test breakpoint transitions

## Layout Issue Resolution

- [ ] Address specific mobile layout issues
  - Fix any content overflow problems
  - Resolve spacing inconsistencies
  - Ensure proper touch target sizes (minimum 44x44 pixels)
  - Check for and fix any z-index conflicts 